text.tspan: Your goal is to fill in gray all the cells of the bottom grid that contain a dot.
Click on cells of the top grids to change their color. The right grid is a copy
of the left one, but shifted. Use the arrows to change the shift.
All the gray cells have to stay inside the grid.
In the bottom grid, cells are gray if they are gray in exactly one of the
1 star: just the 2x2 squares with one square in common
2 stars: something a bit easier than this version
